  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3823330780" />
    <a title="Kath B" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/91662575-kath-b"><img alt="Kath B" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1608186435p2/91662575.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3823330780?book_show_action=true">Feb 13, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kath B" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kath B" href="/user/show/91662575-kath-b">Kath B</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11127415-i-claudius">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3823330780" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15618253840584063113">A wonderful romp through the times of the first three emperors of Rome. This is a gossipy no holds barred tale of vice, corruption, theft and murder all of which the seemingly weak Claudius manages to survive in order to become emperor himself. The characterisations of the key players are marvellously developed to show their descents into evilness and madness as they strive to keep their power. Livia, in particular, the second wife of Augustus and grandmother to Claudius, is a central figure fan</span>
  <span id="freeText15618253840584063113" style="display:none">A wonderful romp through the times of the first three emperors of Rome. This is a gossipy no holds barred tale of vice, corruption, theft and murder all of which the seemingly weak Claudius manages to survive in order to become emperor himself. The characterisations of the key players are marvellously developed to show their descents into evilness and madness as they strive to keep their power. Livia, in particular, the second wife of Augustus and grandmother to Claudius, is a central figure fantastically portrayed as a jealous, scheming and manipulative presence throughout the book. <br /><br />Claudius is the narrator of the book, and, although this is a fictional account, the story line encompasses actual events; battles, policy, marriages and deaths of the times . It is a great read for anyone interested in anything Roman or anyone looking for a tale of intrigue and suspense. Very readable. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15618253840584063113" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


